{"header":"<h1>Parameter <code><span>GenericRelationalValued.Value</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"codex","href":"../../../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Union_Find","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Functional","href":"../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"GenericRelationalValued","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Value","href":"#","kind":"argument-3"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"","content":"<div class=\"odoc-include\"><details open=\"open\"><summary class=\"spec include\"><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">include</span> <a href=\"../../../Parameters/module-type-SIMPLE_GENERIC_VALUE/index.html\">Parameters.SIMPLE_GENERIC_VALUE</a>\u000A  <span class=\"keyword\">with</span> <span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> <span>('a, 'b) <a href=\"../../../Parameters/module-type-SIMPLE_GENERIC_VALUE/index.html#type-relation\">relation</a></span> = <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'b</span>)</span> <a href=\"../argument-2-Relation/index.html#type-t\">Relation.t</a></span></span></span></code></summary><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-relation\"><a href=\"#type-relation\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> <span>('a, 'b) relation</span></span><span> = <span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'b</span>)</span> <a href=\"../argument-2-Relation/index.html#type-t\">Relation.t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>The type of relations, should match <code>GENERIC_MONOID.t</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec type anchored\" id=\"type-t\"><a href=\"#type-t\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">type</span> <span>'a t</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>The generic type of our values. An <code>'a t</code> value is associated to each class of our union find whose representative has type <span class=\"xref-unresolved\" title=\"GENERIC_ELT.t\"><code>'a GENERIC_ELT.t</code></span>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-apply\"><a href=\"#val-apply\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> apply : <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"type-var\">'b</span>)</span> <a href=\"#type-relation\">relation</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'b</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>apply v r</code> is the value obtained by applying relation <code>r</code> to value <code>v</code> <code>apply</code> should be a group action from <span class=\"xref-unresolved\" title=\"GENERIC_GROUP\"><code>R : GENERIC_GROUP with type ('a,'b) t = ('a,'b) relation</code></span> on the value <code>'a t</code>. Meaning it should verify the following:</p><ul><li><code>apply v R.identity = v</code></li><li><code>apply (apply v r2) r1 = apply v (R.compose r2 r1)</code></li></ul></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-meet\"><a href=\"#val-meet\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> meet : <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Intersection of values</p></div></div></details></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-equal\"><a href=\"#val-equal\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> equal : <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> bool</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Equality on values.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-pretty\"><a href=\"#val-pretty\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> pretty : <span><span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Only required for <code>Functional.XX.pretty</code></p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-join\"><a href=\"#val-join\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> join : <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Union of values, only required for <code>Functional.XX.join</code></p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-is_top\"><a href=\"#val-is_top\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> is_top : <span><span><span class=\"type-var\">'a</span> <a href=\"#type-t\">t</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> bool</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Only required for <a href=\"../../index.html\"><code>Functional</code></a>, top values can be removed from the data structure which allows smaller structures and faster access. This function only need to be an over-approximation: it can return <code>false</code> on top, but returning <code>true</code> on non-top leads to precision-loss.</p></div></div>"}